courses.learning_outcomes:
The students will:

•understand the concepts of phylogeny, evolution, and speciation and are able to apply these concepts to explain the diversity of life;
•acquire knowledge on important characteristics distinguishing major groups of living organisms: eubacteria, archebacteria, protists, plants, fungi and animals;
•understand the importance of living organisms to human survival and development of biotechnology, and elaborate with some selected examples;
•understand the theory of human evolution and the interactions between hosts and viruses; and

•appreciate nature and life; and cultivate a responsible attitude toward protection of biodiversity.

學生將會:

•明白有關系統發生、演化和物種形成的概念, 並應用這些概念來解釋生物多樣性;
•獲得能分辨主要生物種類的重要特性的知識, 包括細菌與古細菌、原生生物、植物、 真菌和動物;
•明白各種生物對人類生存及生物科技發展的重要性, 並能以具體例子闡明;
•明白人類進化的理論及寄主與病毒的相互作用; 及
•懂得欣賞大自然和生命; 培養一種對保護生物多樣性的負責任態度

Knowledge outcomes:

1. Acquire core knowledge on transgenic technologies related to plant biotechnology, with more detailed knowledge on new techniques such as marker-free, gene silencing and RNA interference, and gene stacking;
2. Acquire knowledge on potential applications of plant biotechnology;
3. Acquire an educated understanding on the industrial prospective and safety concerns of plant biotechnology.

Skills outcomes:

1. Acquire skills in literature survey using various sources including effective usage of information technologies and web-based searches;
2. Acquire good analytical and oral communication skills via class project presentation;
3. Acquire good problem solving skill via course assessment.

Values and attribute outcomes:

8. Acquire a positive attitude toward plant biotechnology;

9. Acquire an educated mind and responsible attitude to judge the pros and cons of various applications of plant biotechnology to the human society and natural environment.

Knowledge outcomes:
1. Acquire core knowledge on molecular cloning: the concepts of gene cloning, hybridization and blotting, screening and construction of gene libraries.
2. Acquire updated information on DNA sequencing and application of PCR.
3. Acquire ability to understand different approaches to study gene functions.
4. Acquire understanding of organism cloning and transgenic organisms, including the principles and potential applications.
Skills outcomes:
1. Acquire skills in literature survey using various sources including effective usage of information technologies and web-based searches;
2. Acquire good analytical and oral communication skills via class project presentation;
3. Acquire good problem solving skill via course assessment.
Values and attitude outcomes:
1. Acquire a positive attitude toward genetic engineering;
2. Acquire an educated mind and responsible attitude to judge the pros and cons of various applications of genetic engineering to the human society and natural environment.
知識成果:
1. 獲得分子複製的核心知識: 基因複製的概念, 分子雜交與印迹, 基因文庫的建構及篩選;
2. 獲得基因測序和聚合酶連鎖反應應用的最新資訊;
3. 獲得明瞭基因組功能研究不同方法的能力;
4. 獲得對生物複製與轉基因生物的原理和應用理解。

技巧成果:
1. 獲得包括有效利用資訊科技及互聯網搜尋等資源來進行文獻研究的技巧;
2. 通過課程專題報告, 獲得良好的分析及口頭報告技巧;
3. 通過課程考核獲得良好的解決問題的能力。

價值與態度成果:
1. 獲得對遺傳工程的正面態度;
2. 獲得基於知識的思維及負責任的態度, 判斷遺傳工程在人類社會及自然環境所引起的正面及反面作用。
